# cut_markers.manifest -- the "did the merged fix make the cut?" ledger.
#
# Every line is a fix MERGED to a source main that MUST be present in the
# about-to-be-cut artefact. scripts/verify_cut_provenance.sh reads this file and
# blocks the cut (gui/Makefile package + release.sh) if any marker is missing.
# When a new launch-blocking fix lands, add ONE line here -- every future cut is
# then gated on it. This is the mechanism that stops a merged-but-not-shipped fix
# (dead chat, 404 Doctor, unmerged same-org dupes) from recurring.
#
# Format (pipe-delimited, 4 fields):
#   kind | target | pattern | description
#
# kinds:
#   daemon_tag   target=<commit-sha>  pattern=<ignored>  -- the ostler-assistant
#                tag the daemon pin (gui/Makefile DAEMON_VERSION) resolves to MUST
#                contain this commit as an ancestor. Catches a stale daemon
#                tarball (pin says 0.4.8 but the v0.4.8 binary predates the fix).
#   vendor_file  target=<path-rel-CM051>  pattern=<ignored>  -- file must exist.
#   vendor_grep  target=<path-rel-CM051 file OR dir>  pattern=<regex>  -- pattern
#                must be present (grep -rE) under target.
#   assistant_tag_grep  target=<path-rel-ostler-assistant>  pattern=<regex>  --
#                pattern must appear in that file AT the daemon tag the pin
#                resolves to. Gates daemon-side / Hub-UI fixes with no vendored
#                footprint (the web bundle is rebuilt from source at cut time).
#   wiki_image_grep  target=<image-key>:<path-in-image>  pattern=<regex>  --
#                pulls the PINNED wiki Docker digest from install.sh
#                (image-key = wiki-site | wiki-compiler) and greps inside it.
#                FAIL-CLOSED: docker unavailable / pull fail = RED. Ends the
#                manual "did you rebuild the right wiki image" grep dance.
#
# --- v1.0.0 launch blockers (the v0.4.8 walk defects) ---
